text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: The ratio of one quantity to another is a way to express their relative sizes, often in the form of a fraction, where the first quantity

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: is the numerator and the second quantity is the denominator.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 40px; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; cursor: pointer; fill-opacity: 1;

-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: Thus, if p and q are positive quantities, then the ratio of p to q can be written as the fraction p/q

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;

-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: For example, if there are 3 apples and 5 oranges in a basket, we can say that the ratio of the number of apples to the number of oranges is 3/5

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: Like fractions, ratios can be reduced to lowest terms. For example, if there are 8 apples and 12 oranges in a basket,

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: then the ratio of the numbers of apples to oranges is still 2 to 3.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Tahoma; cursor: pointer;

-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;

-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: If three or more positive quantities are being considered, say p, q, and r, then their relative sizes can also be expressed

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: as a ratio with the notation “p to q to r”.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: For example, if there are 5 apples, 30 pears, and 20 oranges in a basket, then the ratio of the numbers of apples to pears to oranges is 5 to 30 to 20

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: This ratio can be reduced to 1 to 6 to 4 by dividing each number by the greatest common divisor of 5, 30, and 20, which is 5.
